An argument against that is that it makes combining multiple `init_randomizers` less succinct. With a shared sha object it'd look like
```
    secp256k1_sha256_initialize(&sha);
    secp256k1_schnorr_verify_init_randomizer(ctx, &ecmult_data.schnorr, &sha, sig, msg32, pk, n_sigs);
    secp256k1_taproot_verify_init_randomizer(ctx, &sha, ...);
    secp256k1_sha256_finalize(&sha, ecmult_data.schnorr.chacha_seed);
```

